---
layout: article
title: Sites
description: "Host web apps on Appwrite Sites from Git: automatic builds, preview URLs, rollbacks, and custom domains. Your traffic can use the Appwrite Network for faster delivery and built-in protections like DDoS mitigation, WAF, and TLS."
back: /docs
---

Appwrite **Sites** hosts the frontend (or full-stack) apps your users open in the browser. It lives in the same project as [Auth](/docs/products/auth), [Databases](/docs/products/databases), and [Functions](/docs/products/functions), so URLs, env vars, and secrets can line up with how you build locally.

Each change can produce a [deployment](/docs/products/sites/deployments). Use [previews](/docs/products/sites/previews) to share a link for a branch or pull request before it goes live. If something goes wrong, [instant rollbacks](/docs/products/sites/instant-rollbacks) point traffic back to a previous version quickly.

Set [domains](/docs/products/sites/domains), [environment variables](/docs/products/sites/environment-variables), and [rendering](/docs/products/sites/rendering) (static, server-rendered, or hybrid) to match your framework. The [Appwrite Network](/docs/products/network) helps with speed and security in front of your site, including TLS and protections like DDoS mitigation and a WAF.

