{% /arrow_link %}

# Core concepts {% #core-concepts %}

These are the primitives for shipping and running a site: builds, URLs, how HTML is rendered, and how you debug when something fails.

{% cards %}
{% cards_item href="/docs/products/sites/deployments" title="Deployments" %}
Track build output, status, and history for every push or manual upload.
{% /cards_item %}
{% cards_item href="/docs/products/sites/previews" title="Previews" %}
Share ephemeral URLs for branches and pull requests before merging.
{% /cards_item %}
{% cards_item href="/docs/products/sites/instant-rollbacks" title="Instant rollbacks" %}
Move production traffic to a known-good deployment in seconds.
{% /cards_item %}
{% cards_item href="/docs/products/sites/domains" title="Domains" %}
Bring your own DNS and certificates for branded URLs.
{% /cards_item %}
{% cards_item href="/docs/products/sites/rendering" title="Rendering" %}
Choose static, SSR, or hybrid rendering models per site.
{% /cards_item %}
{% cards_item href="/docs/products/sites/environment-variables" title="Environment variables" %}
Configure secrets and config per environment the same way you do locally.
{% /cards_item %}
{% cards_item href="/docs/products/sites/logs" title="Logs" %}
Debug builds and runtime issues from the console.
{% /cards_item %}
{% /cards %}

Many teams use **Sites** for the web UI, **Functions** for APIs and webhooks, **Databases** for data, and **Auth** for login - all in one Appwrite project instead of juggling unrelated hosting accounts.

